## Custom CSS (Minimal Use)

Only add custom CSS when Tailwind can't handle it.

```css
/* app/assets/stylesheets/application.tailwind.css */

@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

/* Custom component classes (use sparingly) */
@layer components {
  .btn-primary {
    @apply bg-blue-600 text-white font-semibold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg;
    @apply hover:bg-blue-700 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2;
    @apply transition-colors;
  }
  
  .card {
    @apply bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6;
    @apply hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow;
  }
  
  .input-field {
    @apply w-full px-4 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg;
    @apply focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-blue-500;
  }
}

/* Custom utilities (rare) */
@layer utilities {
  .text-shadow {
    text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  }
  
  .scrollbar-hide {
    -ms-overflow-style: none;
    scrollbar-width: none;
  }
  
  .scrollbar-hide::-webkit-scrollbar {
    display: none;
  }
}
```

**Custom CSS Rules:**
- Always use `@layer` directive
- Use `@apply` with existing Tailwind utilities
- Limit to <100 lines total
- Document why custom CSS is needed
- Prefer Tailwind configuration over custom CSS
